cal traditions. This results in positioning Byatt in the wider literary landscape. This book has broad appeal, including fellow researchers, undergraduate and postgraduate students, plus general enthusiasts of Byatt’s work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aA. S. Byatt.  aChildren's Book.  aMan-Booker shortlist.  acritic.  acritical storytelling.  acritical writings.  ajournalism.  apublic intellectual.  astoryteller.  awriter.1 aAlfer, Alexa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards de Campos, Amy J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779259440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847792594423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847792594/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles